Class ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.DeviceAccessRequest.RequestAccess_ResponseMessage

java.lang.Object

Enclosing class:
ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.DeviceAccessRequest
public class ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.DeviceAccessRequest.RequestAccess_ResponseMessage
extends java.lang.Object

A response message to the ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.DeviceAccessRequest.RequestAccessMessage sent by a provider on the ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.DeviceAccessRequest.RequestAccessMessage.PARAM_msgrACCESSRESULTRECEIVER. If the provider does not respond in a timely manner, the requester may send a new access request or give up. The requester is responsible for closing any open connections it receives even if the response is late. As such, a provider should treat each access request independently, two requests from the same client should be handled the same as two requests one each from different clients. If a provider is granting access, once the response is sent, the provider is free to begin sending messages. It is the requester's responsibility to handle any related timing issues.
